---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Language" description="Learn the language of Vaelinya in small, clear steps.">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles/language-tighten-v20260525.css" />
  <section class="page-section language-page">
    <p class="eyebrow">Language</p>
    <h1>Learn the living words of Vaelinya.</h1>
    <p class="lede">Start with a few living words. The language of Vaelinya should feel like discovery, not homework.</p>
    <p>Follow the words that sit beneath the stories: names, meanings, sounds, and small word-families.</p>

    <article class="visual-callout visual-callout-language">
      <div class="visual-callout-mark" aria-hidden="true"><span>Va</span></div>
      <div class="visual-callout-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">First route</p>
        <h2>Open the public lexicon</h2>
        <p>The lexicon gives each public word slowly: word, pronunciation, IPA, plain meaning, story use, and example sentence.</p>
        <a class="visual-callout-link" href="/language/lexicon/">Open the lexicon</a>
      </div>
    </article>

    <div class="link-list language-route-cards" aria-label="Language routes">
      <a href="/language/lexicon/">
        <strong>Lexicon</strong>
        <span>Start with public words and core meaning.</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/language/lexicon/home-shelter-recovery/">
        <strong>Word families</strong>
        <span>Follow home, shelter, recovery, belonging, and personhood.</span>
      </a>
      <a href="/read/lina/">
        <strong>Words inside Lina’s stories</strong>
        <span>See how language lives inside story use.</span>
      </a>
    </div>

    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Coming next</p>
      <h2>As the public lexicon grows, these routes will open</h2>
      <p>These pages should follow the words, not outrun them.</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Pronunciation</strong> — coming soon.</li>
        <li><strong>Grammar</strong> — coming soon.</li>
        <li><strong>Writing system</strong> — coming soon.</li>
      </ul>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
